    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Abuse of Heroin, All Around</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gerald M Sutliff letter on Apr 24 article holds ignorance and unwise needle use among drug users that is spreading AIDS in Siberia, police corruption and rapidly increasing popularity of heroin are direct results of prohibition</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Heroin Carries AIDS to a Region in Siberia'' (front page, April 24): As your article makes clear, it is not heroin that causes infection with H.I.V., the virus that causes AIDS. Rather, it is ignorance accompanied by needle use.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Heroin Carries AIDS to a Region in Siberia'' (front page, April 24): As your article makes clear, it is not heroin that causes infection with H.I.V., the virus that causes AIDS. Rather, it is ignorance accompanied by needle use.</p>
        <p>Ignorance, unwise needle use, police corruption and the rapidly increasing popularity of heroin are the direct consequences of prohibition.</p>
        <p>GERALD  M. SUTLIFF  Emeryville, Calif., April 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
